The paper discusses the use of spiking neural networks for neuromorphic computing, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The focus of the paper is on the implementation of variable resistive memories as synapses, which is a topic related to electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET). The use of evolutionary algorithms for network design is also discussed, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper evaluates the performance of the networks on a robotic scenario, which is related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of different types of synapses, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG).
